<HEAD>10 Dead In Storm, 700 Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A storm packing 75 mph winds and 15-foot waves has left at least 10 people drowned and another 700 missing, authorities in <LOCATION> Bangladesh </LOCATION> said today. Residents said they had no warning of the storm that developed suddenly in the Bay of <LOCATION> Bengal </LOCATION>. Rescue workers today found nine bodies floating in the bay near the island of <LOCATION> Maheskhali </LOCATION>. One person also died in <LOCATION> Dhaka </LOCATION>, where more than 1,000 were injured, officials said. At least 1,500 people had been reported missing Friday, but district officials said today that about 800 were rescued. Authorities said their search was continuing for the other 700, most of them fishermen. The storm struck almost two months after floods inundated much of <LOCATION> Bangladesh </LOCATION>, killing at least 1,000 people and leaving homeless about 50 million of this impoverished country's 110 million people.
