<BYLINE>By HELENA SMITH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PIRAEUS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A girl was missing today after an Italian freighter rammed a Greek cruise ship carrying 475 British students and teachers, causing the cruise ship to sink, officials said. Two seamen were killed. At least 64 people, including 30 students, were injured Friday evening when the Adige freighter tore a gaping hole in the 6,300-ton Jupiter, which was steaming out of <LOCATION> Piraeus </LOCATION> harbor. Two remained hospitalized today. Screaming children jumped from the listing ship into oil-covered waters before the vessel sank less than an hour after the collision. A British Embassy official said the 14-year-old girl, <PERSON> Vivienne </PERSON> <PERSON> Barley </PERSON>, was the only person still unaccounted for. A <ORGANIZATION> Merchant </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> official said radio appeals were broadcast `` for anyone who may have seen her or picked her up to contact us.'' Frogmen and <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> officials searched the area where the Epirotiki Lines cruise ship sank less than a mile from <LOCATION> Piraeus </LOCATION> harbor on the start of an eight-day educational cruise. `` The Italian ship tore a huge hole below the waterline, almost splitting the Jupiter in two ... no wonder it sank in less than an hour,'' said <PERSON> Spyros </PERSON> <PERSON> Mavrikis </PERSON>, an Epirotiki spokesman. Greek Prime Minister <PERSON> Andreas </PERSON> <PERSON> Papandreou </PERSON>, looking fit and well after major heart surgery in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, flew to <LOCATION> Athens </LOCATION> today promising a full investigation into the collision. At the time of the accident, the 415 teen-agers and their 60 teachers and helpers were on a trip to Greek islands and ports in <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Turkey </LOCATION>. `` I was sitting with my friends in the lounge when we looked out of the windo