<HEAD>45 Injured in Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A fire destroyed a plastics factory Saturday and injured at least 45 people, 20 of them critically, police said. The fire was caused by an explosion of a gas cyclinder inside the factory, said a police officer who spoke on condition of anonymity. The officer said the factory was operating without a license. `` The plastic factory was located inside a grain depot -LRB- warehouse -RRB-, we did not know it was functioning,'' he said. The factory was in the northwestern part of the city. The official said of the injured, seven were not expected to survive. At least 100 firefighters fought the blaze for three hours and brought it under control.
