problems makes no sense. I wo n't permit any personnel changes'' in Solidarity's proposed delegation. `` I like the general very much, and I am ready -LRB- to talk -RRB-, but the talk can not concern personnel problems or problems of Solidarity and pluralism,'' he said. `` This is all for the round-table.'' <PERSON> Walesa </PERSON> said the opposition could start the talks immediately if the government agreed. `` I'm not going to travel and talk without a purpose, but I'm ready to talk about the important things,'' he said Urban said: `` There are various problems: who should issue invitations, where it takes place, how many working groups there will be. ... We also need to discuss and remove controversies concerning the personnel composition. `` We strongly appeal -LRB- to the opposition -RRB- not to avoid the necessary preparatory work so that the round-table can finally meet,'' Urban said. <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> mediator <PERSON> Andrzej </PERSON> <PERSON> Stelmachowski </PERSON>, who met with Politiburo member <PERSON> Jozef </PERSON> <PERSON> Czyrek </PERSON> on Saturday, said only one major obstacle remained. He said the government seeks to remove two people from Solidarity's proposed delegation to the talks. Urban previously said there were problems with the proposed participation of longtime Solidarity advisers <PERSON> Adam </PERSON> <PERSON> Michnik </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jacek </PERSON> <PERSON> Kuron </PERSON>, who in the government's view advocate the overthrow of communism.
