<TEXT>
 Rep. <PERSON> Gary </PERSON> <PERSON> Ackerman </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.Y. </LOCATION>, also felt good. <PERSON> Ackerman </PERSON> used to weigh more than 280 pounds. He dieted. He exercised. And, in triumph, he went to the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> floor to announce he had lost more than 100 pounds. `` The <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> historian has confirmed that my weight loss is the biggest of any member of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> in history,'' the congressman crowed.
